    text: "A person cannot inherit based on law or a will, nor gain any benefit from a will (is deemed unworthy):\n\n1) anyone who intentionally caused the death of the decedent, or attempted to do so;\n\n2) anyone who, through coercion, threat, or fraud, induced the decedent to create or revoke a will or any of its provisions, or prevented him from doing so;\n\n3) anyone who, with the intent of preventing the decedent's last wishes, destroyed or concealed his will, or forged it;\n\n4) anyone who has seriously violated the legal obligation to support the decedent, or denied him necessary assistance;\n\n5) (no longer valid by the decision of the USRS).\n\nThe court examines unworthiness ex officio.",
