    text: "The fourth order of inheritance consists of the decedent's great-grandparents.\n\nThe decedent's great-grandparents from the father's side inherit in equal parts half of the estate, while the other half is inherited in equal parts by the decedent's great-grandparents from the mother's side.\n\nIf any of these ancestors cannot or will not inherit, his share is inherited by his spouse, if he is the decedent's ancestor.\n\nIf a pair of ancestors from the same lineage cannot or will not inherit, their share is inherited by another pair of ancestors from the same lineage.\n\nIf the great-grandparents from one lineage cannot or will not inherit, their share is inherited by the great-grandparents from another lineage.",
